  "texts": [
    "This definition may be used to analyze an object's measurements and determine which group the leaf falls to; the process of classifying crop diseases involves taking information from infected plant leaves and determining the differences in colour between diseased and healthy crop leaves (Halder et al. (2018)).",
    "It is either supervised or unsupervised and uses a variety of techniques, including colour information, image borders, or image segmentation.",
    "Crop disease severity is defined as the portion or percentage of visible diseased crop tissue relative to the total amount of crop tissue.",
    "In contrast to the total number of crops affected, it is a continuous variable with two binary values of zeros and ones that represent the degree of crop tissue quality.",
    "Bock (2022) identifies it as the crop unit of quantity showing perceptible disease symptoms, which is frequently expressed as a percentage."
  ],
